        <definition>GazeVector3 Gaze::GazeBasis3D::get_euler_gaze_model_deg</definition>
        <argsstring>() const</argsstring>
        <name>get_euler_gaze_model_deg</name>
        <qualifiedname>Gaze::GazeBasis3D::get_euler_gaze_model_deg</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Decomposes the basis into standard ZYX Euler angles (pitch, yaw, roll in degrees). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Standard ZYX decomposition that restricts the yaw to [-90, 90] degrees (choosing the branch where cos(yaw) &gt; 0). Used specifically for feeding inputs to the ONNX gaze model which expects a standard coordinate convention (yaw centered around 0 degrees). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
